            "fact_text": "<p>Ethical & Conflict FreeTraditional labour intensive diamond mining, while regulated in many regions now, has been historically linked to financing conflict in politically unstable areas, human rights violations, unsafe and forced labour conditions among other ethical issues. While initiatives such as Kimberley Process try to control the trade of conflict diamonds and trace their origins, the complex nature of global supply chains cannot guarantee total traceability of every natural stone. Being ethical, sustainable, and conflict free is one of the most well known advantages of owning a lab grown diamond. These lab created gems completely eliminate these concerns. These gems are formed in hitech controlled lab environments, offering complete traceability from start to finish. These diamonds are an ethical choice, from their origin to their purchase. There are no human rights violations, or risks of contributing to conflict zones, displacement of communities and natural habitats, or environmental concerns. If you’re someone who values ethical purchases, social responsibility and sustainability, lab grown diamonds are made just for you! As society continues to make sustainability and ethical purchases a priority in their buying decisions, lab grown diamonds continue to grow in popularity.</p>"
