            "fact_text": "<p>Consistency & Quality ControlThe creation of lab grown diamonds provides the greatest advantage in that they are created under the greatest degree of quality control and consistency. Unlike natural diamonds, which are subject to natural variations (including inclusions, tints or irregularities that cannot be controlled by humans), lab created diamonds are created in controlled environments that allow the manufacturers to control every aspect of the diamond's formation, including temperature, pressure and growth conditions. Lab created diamonds typically have fewer impurities and more consistent clarity and colour than natural diamonds because of the controlled environment in which they are created.As a result of the superior quality of lab created diamonds, the consumer will have a greater chance of finding the diamond that meets all of his/her desired specifications, including shape, colour, and carat weight; this is particularly true for diamonds that would otherwise be very rare or highly priced in nature.Because lab created diamonds are produced under consistent conditions, many lab created diamonds exhibit unparalleled brilliance and visual purity. Additionally, all lab created diamonds are graded using the same international standards as natural diamonds, providing consumers with complete confidence in their authenticity and value.</p>"
